sequenceDiagram
    participant KFP as KFP Pipeline Runner
    participant DD as dataset_download Pod
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 / MinIO<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PVC as Shared PVC<br/>Filesystem
    participant TM as train_model Pod
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Trainer as Kubeflow Trainer<br/>(TrainingHub)
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Workers as Training Worker Pods
    participant Eval as universal_llm_evaluator Pod
    participant MReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over KFP,MReg: Flow 1: LLM Fine-Tuning Pipeline (OSFT/SFT/LoRA)

        KFP->>DD: Step 1: Launch dataset_download<br/>KFP ServiceAccount
        DD->>HF: GET datasets/models<br/>TLS 1.2+ / HF_TOKEN Bearer
        HF-->>DD: Dataset artifacts
        DD->>S3: GET objects (alternative)<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS IAM
        S3-->>DD: Data files
        DD->>PVC: Write prepared dataset<br/>Chat-format validated, train/eval split

        KFP->>TM: Step 2: Launch train_model<br/>KFP ServiceAccount
        TM->>K8sAPI: Submit TrainingJob<br/>TLS 1.2+ / Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>Trainer: Create TrainingJob CR
        Trainer->>Workers: Spawn distributed workers
        Workers->>OCI: Pull OCI model (optional)<br/>TLS 1.2+ / Docker config.json
        OCI-->>Workers: Model artifacts
        Workers->>PVC: Read dataset, write checkpoints
        Workers-->>TM: Job completed

        KFP->>Eval: Step 3: Launch evaluator<br/>KFP ServiceAccount
        Eval->>PVC: Load trained model
        Note over Eval: Run lm-eval harness<br/>with vLLM backend<br/>(GPU required)
        Eval->>PVC: Write evaluation metrics

        KFP->>MReg: Step 4: Launch model_registry<br/>KFP ServiceAccount
        Note over MReg: Register model with<br/>provenance & metrics
        MReg-->>KFP: Registration complete<br/>HTTP 8080 (plaintext, no auth)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over KFP,S3: Flow 2: AutoGluon Tabular Training Pipeline

        participant DL as automl_data_loader Pod
        participant Split as tabular_train_test_split Pod
        participant Select as models_selection Pod
        participant Refit as autogluon_models_full_refit Pod
        participant LB as leaderboard_evaluation Pod

        KFP->>DL: Step 1: Launch data_loader<br/>KFP ServiceAccount
        DL->>S3: GET CSV data<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS IAM (boto3)
        S3-->>DL: CSV data (up to 1GB)
        DL->>PVC: Write loaded data

        KFP->>Split: Step 2: Train/test split
        Split->>PVC: Read data, write splits

        KFP->>Select: Step 3: Model selection<br/>AutoGluon stacking/bagging
        Select->>PVC: Read train data, write models

        KFP->>Refit: Step 4: Full refit<br/>Top-N models on full dataset
        Refit->>PVC: Read full data, write refitted models

        KFP->>LB: Step 5: Leaderboard evaluation
        LB->>PVC: Read models, write leaderboard
    end
